Hoping to capitalize on the success of OPEC, Russia, Iran and Qatar are discussing creating a natural gas cartel. Together, these three countries make up 60% of the world's natural gas supply. Source: TrulyNewsworthy.com
 
 Russia has already used their natural gas prowess to bully Europe. If they did create this new cartel just imagine the chaos and power grabbing that would ensue. This is just another reason for the U.S., and really the rest of the world, to get over their reliance on foreign energy.
